
Execute actions on 'rkt' mode. For example:

eveadm rkt list

Usage:
  eveadm rkt [flags]
  eveadm rkt [command]

Available Commands:
  create      Run shell command with arguments in 'create' action on 'rkt' mode
  delete      Run shell command with arguments in 'delete' action on 'rkt' mode
  info        Run shell command with arguments in 'info' action on 'rkt' mode
  list        Run shell command with arguments in 'list' action on 'rkt' mode
  start       Run shell command with arguments in 'start' action on 'rkt' mode
  stop        Run shell command with arguments in 'stop' action on 'rkt' mode
  update      Run shell command with arguments in 'update' action on 'rkt' mode

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for rkt

Global Flags:
      --config string             config file (default is $HOME/.eveadm.yaml)
      --dir string                RKT data dir
      --insecure-options string   RKT insecure-options (default "image")
      --stage1-type string        Type of stage1 (xen or general) (default "xen")
  -t, --timeout string            Actions timeout in minutes
  -v, --verbose                   Verbose execution

Use "eveadm rkt [command] --help" for more information about a command.
